rComments: Amazing prof! So sweet, and wants you to succeed. Her quizzes can be a little specific sometimes so it is important to read her textbook well.

As an immersion student, the amount of reading in this course was very challenging. You'll have to take notes from TopHat if you want to really understand-I find the lectures are a surface-level intro do the modules you'll have to read-and that's where you'll learn the most This prof is an overall sweetheart and I don't have much to say about her.

Prof Lemarec is a solid choice for an introductory course. Her lectures are good if you want more clarity on the material but you honestly don't need to go as long as you do TopHat. Tests have no surprises, it's everything you can find easily in your notes. The only downside is she talks fast so I don't recommend her for french immersion students.

This was my second class with LeMarec and I would take more of her classes if I could. Her lectures are definitely heavy and you absolutely need to pay full attention, I still learned so much in her class and you can tell she really cares about her students. This class isn't an easy A but is definitely worth it. Would recommend.

I took her 2701 bio class and as someone who doesn't really excell in sciences I thought her teaching was clear and concise. She gives an opportunity to raise your grade and tries to make the class intersting. I would take again.

she frankly does not deserve those bad reviews. Really caring and gise us EVERYTHING we need to pass. very versatile and give so many opportunities to get better grades if we are falling behind. she does speak fast in class, but everything is in PowerPoint and there are also videos and audio attached to the PP. no final exam 3group Proj 7mini quiz.

The worst prof I've ever had. Doesn't care about her students, her quizzes are difficult for no reason. speaks way too fast and speaks about things that aren't even necessary to the course. I do not recommend this class with her.

Such a sweet lady, but do not take her class if it's in English. It's difficult to understand her slides (which I think may be translated using an online source from french to english), and it's hard to follow in class. Kind of disorganized. Her exams are also confusing because of the language barrier. A- because of group presentations.

very caring and wants to see all her student succeed. lectures are heavy and a bit different than other PSY classes this one is more like a biology class. If you did Biology in 12th grade it will make this class a lot easier for you. Her exams are fair, usually MCQs and short answers. Has a strong french accent and needs a bit to get used too

Très désorganisée. Examens aucunement en lien avec ce qui a été vu en classe. Examens hyper difficiles. J'avais de la difficulté à comprendre. parle beaucoup et ne mentionne pas ce qui est important. À NE PAS PRENDRE

Excellent professor for students who are interested in furthering studies in psychology. She makes herself available to her students and cares about their success! Unfortunately, many students will not like her teaching style because she teaches ADULTS, so anyone who feels they need to be babied will not enjoy.
Her classes are hard to follow. She's very disorganized and doesn't present the information clearly. Very hard exams. Just dont take her class. Like dont.

Unclear exam questions (with many mistakes as well). She's a bad teacher overall and simply not qualified to teach PSY3571. She doesn't have clinical experience and it reflects on her teaching. You have to study EXTREMELY hard to get a good grade and prepare for trick questions on the exams. Penalizes students that dont show up to class.

This professor doesn't have the students' best interest at heart. She will voluntarily penalize her students by asking questions referring to information that she mentionned only once in class. Her exams are extremely heavy. You need to study at least a month in advance to feel fully prepared. She is not qualified to teach PSY 3571.

She is very nice and available if you have questions. However, her lectures were often hard to follow as she speaks very quickly and then tests on what she said in class. Had three big group case studies but she was not specific at all in the instructions, making it very hard to do well. Would not take her again
Just avoid her

C'est un bon prof, surtout pour ceux ayant pris des cours préalables en sciences (bio/anatomie). Elle peut être difficile à suivre mais habituellement les explications sont claires et elle est intéressante. Elle veut vraiment le mieux pour les élèves et elle est super flexible pour les dates d'échéances (ex: 2 dates pour notre premier mid-term)
Worst but worst teacher ever! She's rude when you ask questions in class and never answers emails! Her questions on her exams are too complicated and they could be easier.
Class is boring but the teacher is passionate. You need to study

Does not talk very loud, hard to understand especially with her French accent. Very monotone. Overall wouldn't recommend this prof and the class. If you want to take a PSY class, take PSY1502 with Julie Marcil, she's great!
Elle est très gentille, les cours magistraux sont plaisants bien qu'ennuyeux parfois. Les examens réflètent bien la matière apprise en cours et elle est disponible en tout temps.
Very boring I found, doesn't talk loud enough if you're sitting in the back. Power points are very unorganized. Her french can be hard to follow. Overall just not a fan.
Examens difficiles et BEAUCOUP de matière. Si tu ne connais pas ta matière tu n'auras pas de bonnes notes. Prof est gentille mais enseigne très rapidement.
Very nice and she knows her stuff but TOUGH grader, especially 4th year !!  Her exams are hard.
Fun class! Human prof, she is an actual person talking to students :) Not just a robot prof only interested in research.  Available to help!

The class itself was a summer class, so I knew the workload was already going to be tough. The 2 midterms are only on the in-class material and the final exam is only on the Manual. So make sure you space your time right to read through the necessary chapters, or else you'll have trouble passing the class. She always had a smile on her face. :)

Great prof! Classes are awesome if you're interested by the material. Gives you the exact structure of the exam (usually MCQ, few 2 pointers that you choose from, 5 point question(s), 10 point question(s) usually get to choose between 2 and gives you the percentage of each section of exam). Only bad thing is randomness of some questions (2pointers)

I absolutly loved her! I had taken this class in previously and had a horrible prof so i took this class again and I am so glad I did! She is very kind and very helpful! Her exams are very easy. All you need is the book for the final and her slides for the midterm and you're good to go. My favorite prof so far!
She Knows her course material, but she asked a lot for the exams. Get ready to memorize!
Elle est très gentille et prête à aider les étudiants qui l'on besoin. Elle a beaucuop de connaissances au sujet de la matière. Donne beaucuop d'info supplimentaire, finale été difficile.

Sleep and Dream (French), very interesting class and good prof. Helpful and understanding of student needs. Textbook was PDF and was free on Virtual Campus. Exam was fair but a little bit harder than other courses I have had with her. Went over exams in class and could write down any parts we disagreed with for review. Overall it was great.

Good prof, very helpful and will go over concepts more than once if students do not understand. Also very helpful during projects, finds great articles relating to your subject for you, helps to get the project started. Exam and fair and straightforward, no tricks.

Such a nice lady! Truly cares for students and their understanding of the material. Will go over concepts 10 times if needed - and she is always nice about it. Powerpoints are lenghty (and usually full of typos) but everything is there; allows for easy studying. Exam are very fair. Study and you will do well! Overall, great prof AND lovely person!
Drugs and behaviour (french). Had her for another class too but this one is by far the best, can tell she likes what she is teaching
Great Prof! Cares about students and is helpful. Likes what she teachers.
By far one of my favourite profs I've had in university! This was my 3rd time having her & she's amazing! Very knowledgeable about psychology/neuroanatomy & a very fair grader!
She is terrible and is always seems lost. She is nice and trying but for me it did not work. Slides are incomplete but she takes way to fast and it is hard to take notes.

Elle enseigne plutôt bien, elle sait se faire comprendre par les élèves en donnant de bons exemples. Par contre elle lit le powerpoint tout le cours ce qui rend parfois le cours ennuyeux. Par contre les labs sont très intéressants à faire.
BORING CLASS!!! She just reads her slides... its hard to understand her with her strong accent!!

Quand l'on s'attarde vraiment à ce qu'elle dit, ses cours sont vraiment intéressants. Par contre, je me suis endormi dans certaines de ses classes. Les mi-termes sont faciles si vous faites les questions sur le campus virtuel et vous lisez et comprenez bien ses diaporamas. Ils sont bien détaillés. Vous n'avez pas besoin de lire le livre pour passer
Really good prof, she explains really well and she is very available! :)

she means very well and will do anything to help you out, but she is very monotone. if you try your best to listen, her notes are good, but doesnt explain much more than the slide. exams are straight forward.
boring.. only reads her slides...
She's alright.

If you know your science, expect to find a lot of mistakes in her notes. She's not very knowledgable. I will say one thing to her advantage, she's really nice and always willing to help. Most people find her boring but I actually enjoyed her lectures, maybe it's just because I love the subject.
OMG! she doesn't know anything about the class material. When a student asks a question and the teacher says "i don't know", and doesn't look into it any further you know its a bad teacher.
Stupid class, she didn't seem to know how to explain anything with any clarity.  Only reads her notes and those even have errors.
OMG, Boring. She really needs to learn not to just read the note that she puts on the internet. Its a good class to sleep during, because you'll be able to understand fine by reading the book!
EEk!

She means well but not very organised and leaves students with a blank look of confusion.  Since she gives us all our notes on the internet and simply reads the same notes in class... it's a bit pointless to even have her there!
